%I A114307 #10 Mar 29 2026 23:48:03
%S A114307 12,60,300,3000,30000,300000,3000000,30000000,300000000,3000000000,
%T A114307 30000000000,300000000000,3000000000000,30000000000000,
%U A114307 300000000000000,3000000000000000,30000000000000000,300000000000000000,3000000000000000000
%N A114307 Length of the cycle for Lucas numbers mod 10^n.
%C A114307 This is the length of the cycle for final n decimal digits in Lucas numbers (A000032).
%H A114307 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/LucasNumber.html">Lucas Number</a>.
%H A114307 <a href="/index/Rec#order_01">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (10).
%F A114307 a(n) = 3*10^(n-1) for n>2; a(1)=12, a(2)=60.
%F A114307 a(n) = lcm(3*2^(n-1),4*5^(n-1)). In particular, for n>=3, a(n) = 3*10^(n-1). - _Max Alekseyev_, May 17 2006
%F A114307 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Mar 28 2026: (Start)
%F A114307 G.f.: 12*x*(1 - 5*x - 25*x^2)/(1 - 10*x).
%F A114307 E.g.f.: (3/10)*(exp(10*x) - 1) + 3*x*(3 + 5*x).
%F A114307 a(n) = 10*a(n-1) for n > 3.
%F A114307 a(n) = A096363(n)/5. (End)
%e A114307 L(i) mod 10 = L(i+12) mod 10; L(i) mod 10^2 = L(i+a(2)) mod 10^2; L(i) mod 10^3 = L(i+a(3)) mod 10^3;
%Y A114307 Cf. A000032, A001175, A096363.
%K A114307 base,easy,nonn,changed
%O A114307 1,1
%A A114307 Jerzy Podgorski (j.podgorski(AT)pollub.pl), May 14 2006; corrected May 16 2006
%E A114307 More terms from _Max Alekseyev_, May 17 2006
